WHAT IS IT?
-----------

  'Noel_Q' is a Workbench game that is played like a normal 'Solo'
or 'Hi-Q' game in which you move a peg to an empty space. The
playing rule is simple: you must move a peg two spaces
horizontally or diagonally. The game features two playing mode,
a "Normal" and an "Inverted" play:

-In the 'Normal' play, you jump over a peg and that peg will be
 removed. Try to remove all the pegs until only one is left,
 preferably where the empty space was located at the start.

-In the 'Inverted' play, you jump over an empty space and a peg
 will appear there. Try to 'fill' up the board until only one
 empty space is left, preferably where the peg was located at
 the start.

  The main feature of the game is the 'Christmas theme': the shape
of the game board is patterned in the form of a Christmas tree,
and the pegs are randomly coloured (to simulate coloured lights or
ornaments) using the colour palette of the Workbench.

  When you get bored with the coloured pegs (or if you play the
game after Christmas :) there is an option which selects the
"white" (normal) pegs.

  Have fun!

